{
  "summary": "The text refers to the writings of Saint Jerome in his commentary on Ezekiel, where he explains the symbolic days that represent years in a prophecy concerning the iniquities of the houses of Israel and Judah. These days are thought to total 430 years of captivity, which some Jews believed marked the duration of their current tribulation, starting from the capture of Jerusalem by the Romans under Vespasian. This belief paralleled the biblical account of the Israelites' 430-year sojourn in Egypt as stated in Exodus.",
  "keywords": ["Anti-Judaism", "Typology", "Temple"]
}
